  "translations": {
    "en": "He said: And Abul Hasan al-Rahbi the grammarian recited to me the following verses by al-Hajjaj ibn Yusuf al-Tamimi: \"Indeed a man who has lived fifty years is truly near to the watering-place of his return. When you pass a day alone in your life, do not say 'I am alone,' but rather say 'Over me is an observer.' When the generation in which you lived has passed, and you are left behind in a new generation, then you are a stranger.\"",
